message.content: cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.IR. The paper focuses on natural language processing and machine learning techniques for question generation, which are commonly studied in the sub-categories of computational linguistics (cs.CL), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also incorporates linguistic features related to named entity recognition and entity coreference resolution, which are relevant to natural language understanding (cs.NE). Finally, the paper evaluates its model on a benchmark dataset for question generation, which falls under information retrieval (cs.IR).
